SIMPLE: electrical_light
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Electrical light
<hw>Electrical light</hw>, <sn>1.</sn> <def>the light produced by a
current of electricity which in passing through a resisting medium heats
it to incandescence or burns it. See under <er>Carbon</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a lamp whose light is produced by passing an
electric current through a light bulb, especially an incandescent
lamp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>electric chair</ent>⟦br⟧
